description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A service that delivers excellence as standard&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It’s a great work environment with much better opportunities than my previous unit.”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Amelia Clancy, Band 5 staff nurse&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen as a Band 5 staff nurse to fulfil your potential at one of our Intensive Care units. Let your skills and experience shine in an environment where excellent service is a way of life. We offer genuine opportunities to progress your career in Intensive Care, with one of the largest portfolios of services in the UK that includes more than 50 specialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hospital is a leading specialist centre in Neurosciences, complex ENT, Urology, Cancer and a busy Emergency Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We value our staff and commit to helping you achieve your full potential. We guarantee learning and development supported by our highly trained team of nurses, our medical team, and our well-resourced critical care clinical education team. Each new Band 5 will be allocated to a team and supported by their own mentor, co-mentor and team leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our Band 5 pathway includes the following opportunities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;foundation to critical care programme for you to build-up confidence and experience &lt;br /&gt;• rotate across different Intensive Care units to obtain experience in specialties &lt;br /&gt;• nationally recognised training using the Intensive Care network ‘step’ competencies &lt;br /&gt;• internationally recognised critical care course&lt;br /&gt;• simulation training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;clinical coaching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotating opportunities across all four of our Intensive Care units includes cardiac, major trauma, neuro and general.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By choosing a career in Intensive Care with us, you can tap into a range of exciting opportunities that could inspire you to work in clinical education, organ donation, or to become an outreach practitioner, an advanced nurse practitioner or a site nurse practitioner. And at Imperial College Healthcare you’ll be working with leading clinicians pushing boundaries in patient care. You’ll get an experience like no other that will fast forward your career. Our staff include RCN nurse of the year and rising star.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include opportunities for career development, flexible working and well being, plus a staff recognition scheme. You can also take advantage of optional benefits including the cycle to work or car lease schemes, season ticket loan or membership options for onsite leisure facilities. All of our hospitals have quick transport access to Westfield shopping and leisure centre, the West End, and a range of local bars, cafes and restaurants – ideal for team socials!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
